"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-confirmed-time-sa-team-will-be-in-paris-olympics-4x100m-relay-final\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbConfirmed: Time South Africa will be in Olympics 4x100m relay final  Here is the time when you can catch the South African team race for a medal in the men's 4x100m relay final on Friday.  Team South Africa automatically progressed through to the Men's 4x100m relay final after finishing second in their Olympics heat on Thursday, with super star Akana Simbine producing a stunning final leg.  With Benjamin Richardson out injured, the team had to reshuffle the order, taking starter Shaun Maswanganyi to the second leg on the back straight, while youngster Bayanda Walaza started with Bradley Nkoana running the bend.  However, it was Simbine - in his usual anchor role - who shot past several competitors in the final straight to to finish second in 37.94 sec to secure a spot in Friday's final.  The Olympics 4x100m relay final will take place around 19:45 on Friday night.  For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section for free-to-read content  Team SAare involved in four sports at the 2024 Paris Olympics on Thursday. There is women's golf, diving, sport climbing and athletics on the programme.  The United States (27 golds) lead China (also 25 golds), Australia (18), France (13) and Great Britain in the medal standings. Team SA are 37th with one gold (Tatjana Smith), one silver (Smith) and two bronzes (men's Sevens rugby and Alan Hatherly).  COMPLETED  ATHLETICS  Women's 100m hurdles, round 1:Marion Fourie (pictured) finished 4th in her heat in 12.91 to qualify 21st overall and she advances to the repechage stage  Women's javelin qualification, Group A:Jo-Ane van Dyk qualified automatically for the final with her opening throw of 64.22m, which was all she needed to top the group  Men's 800m, heats:Edmund du Plessis finished 2nd in his heat in 1:45.73 to comfortably qualify for the semi-finals  Men's high jump qualification, Group B:Brian Raats produced a best jump of 2.24m, at his first attempt at the height, and he qualified for the final  Men's 200m, semi-finals:Shaun Maswanganyi finished 4th in his semi-final in 20.42 and missed out on a place in the final  Men's 200m, semi-finals:Wayde van Niekerk finished 7th in his semi-final in 20.72 and missed out on a place in the final  Women's 400m, semi-finals:Miranda Coetzee finished 8th in her semi-final and missed out on a place in the final  CANOEING  Women's kayak, single 500m heats:Esti Olivier finished 5th in her heat in 1:55.98 and progressed to the quarter-finals  Women's kayak, single 500m quarter-final:Esti Olivier finished 6th in her heat in 1:53.21 and did not progress to the semi-finals  Women's kayak, single 500m heats:Tiffany Koch finished 6th in 2:02.76 and qualified for the quarter-finals  Women's kayak, single 500m quarter-final:Tiffany Koch finished 6th in her heat in 1:56.81 and did not progress to the semi-finals  Men's kayak, single 1000m heats:Hamish Lovemore finished 3rd in his heat and qualified for the quarter-finals  Men's kayak, single 1000m heats:Andrew Birkett finished 5th in his heat and qualified for the quarter-finals  Men's kayak, single 1000m quarter-finals:Hamish Lovemore finished 2nd in his heat in 3:36.64 and qualified for the semi-finals. Andrew Burkett was 3rd in the same heat in 3:28.11 and was unable to progress to the semi-finals  CYCLING  Men's sprint, qualifying:Jean Spies finished 29th in qualifying with a time of 9.962 (av speed 72.275 km/h) and did not progress to the 1/32 finals  GOLF  Women's individual, first round:Ashleigh Buhai is sitting in 2nd position after firing an opening round of 68, four-under-par. Paula Reto carded a six-over round of 78  DIVING  Women's 3m springboard prelims:Julia Vincent qualified for the semi-finals of the competition with a combined score of 283.50. She finished 12th and goes through as one of the top 18  SKATEBOARDING  Men's Park, prelims:Dallas Oberholzer had a best score of 33.83, which saw him finish 23rd overall and he did not progress to the semi-finals  SPORT CLIMBING  Men's boulder & Lead, semi-final Lead:Mel Janse van Rensburg added 7.1 Lead points to his boulder points 9.4 for a total of 16.5. He finished 20th and did not progress to the final  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observ